HEADWORD: Temporo-
<hw>Tem"po*ro-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A combining form used in anatomy
to indicate <xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation to</xex>,
<xex>the temple</xex>, or <xex>temporal bone</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>temporo</ex>facial</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

